Adilabad Municipality and the District Food Inspector on Thursday organised an awareness meeting for fruit whole sellers and retail vendors on the ban on ripening fruits artificially by using calcium carbide.About 100 vendors and whole sellers attended the programme which was conduced by District Food Inspector E. Balaji and Municipal Food Inspector Md. Ayaz.The fruit sellers were told about the penalty on violation of the ban, besides the health damage that artificially ripened fruits cause.They were also apprised of the governmentâ€™s move to sanction fruit ripening chambers on subsidy.